Welcome to
My mission at Axis for Health is to support people in finding their unique ‘root’ to make healthy lifestyle choices to improve vitality, energy and overall wellbeing as they transition through the various stages of life.
Are you over 40, tired of feeling tired and sick of making eating habit changes but never achieving your goal?

Grab your free ebook to start your journey NOW.

I will guide you in finding your ‘root’ to wellness to live the abundant life you richly deserve. My key function within Axis for Health, is to provide you with programs to address gastrointestinal related symptoms which includes IBS, reflux and bloating. As well as tackling hormonal imbalances, sleep issues and migraines.

Your health goals and symptom relief will be achieved through easy realistic nutritional and lifestyle strategies. In addition sunlight, rest, water, spirituality, temperance, exercise, air are other laws of health to be adhered to in achieving optimal health.
Life is like a tree. We see the beauty, the ever-changing canopies of leaves, but we fail to remember the foundation and the roots that feed the tree.

ABOUT US
WHY SEE A NUTRITIONAL THERAPIST?
Nutritional therapy works for everyone; young or old. Whether you have a specific health concern that you want to address, or simply want to check that you are on the right track to healthy eating, a nutritional therapist can help in your goal towards identifying foods and lifestyle choices that can help you to look and feel your best.

ONE SIZE DOES NOT FIT ALL
One of the fundamental beliefs for my practice is that there is no ‘one size fits all’ diet; likewise, there is no one health treatment which would benefit all persons at every stage of their life.

ONE-TO-ONE CONSULTATION
A one-to-one consultation is delivered to ascertain the health issues of prospective clients a tailored plan suited to their needs and health goals is then crafted.
15 minutes
Click for Free
Consultation
Evidence has proved that good health begins with what you put into the body.

In addition, sunlight, rest, water, exercise, air and spirituality are the other laws of health that cannot be excluded as being pivotal elements when thriving for optimal health.
The principles of Functional Medicine are utilised, the aim is to look for the root cause of disease in an individual, and how and why this has happened.

Symptoms are not looked at individually, as an isolated bodily system; the whole person is looked at.
I support my clients to adopt a healthy lifestyle that works for them; providing the tools to feel confident to do this independently, on a long term basis.

Wholesome, unprocessed foods are promoted, for optimal wellbeing, alongside utilising the therapeutic effects of specific foods, in order to support specific health concerns.
